## [ Visual Studio ]
# User-specific files
*.rsuser
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates

# Ignore sensitive configuration files
**/appsettings.json
**/appsettings.Development.json

# Build results
[Dd]ebug/
[Dd]ebugPublic/
[Rr]elease/
x64/
x86/
[Aa]rm/
[Aa]rm64/
bld/
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/
[Ll]og/
[Ll]ogs/

## [ .NET / ASP.NET Core ]
# User-secrets and Local Settings
appsettings.Development.json
appsettings.Local.json
secrets.json

# Temporary files created by .NET
.templateengine/
.librarymanager/
.vs/
.idea/

# NuGet Packages
*.nupkg
# The packages folder is usually omitted because it's restored on build
**/[Pp]ackages/*
!**/[Pp]ackages/repositories.config

## [ Frontend / Tools ]
# Node.js (if using Angular/React/LibMan)
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*

# Static assets folders that are auto-generated
wwwroot/lib/

## [ OS Specific ]
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

## [ Custom Uploads Folder ]
# Since your project saves files to "Uploads/", you should ignore the 
# content but keep the folder.
/Uploads/*
!/Uploads/.gitkeep
